    "narrative": "Ghost Ride the WHIP enters today\u2019s slate with a high-floor offensive deployment, led by **Mickey Moniak**, who claims the day\u2019s top efficiency rating at 75.98. **Moniak** benefits from an elite combination of a favorable hitter\u2019s park and a prime #2 spot in the order against Tyler Glasnow; crucially, the matchup against a pitcher with a 100% SB allowance rate provides a massive boost for our pursuit of the league's scarcest category. **Tyler Soderstrom** (72.72) and **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** (72.09) follow closely, both capitalizing on favorable park factors and the exploitable Davis Martin and Michael Wacha, respectively. While **Chisholm Jr.** faces a minor headwind that tempers his ceiling, the significant SP skill advantage provides enough margin to keep him as a locked-in start despite the 31% rain risk in that stadium.\n\nStrategic benching remains disciplined, with **Alex Freeland** serving as the most difficult omission. With a score of 58.63, **Freeland** was ultimately edged out by the superior power-hitting matchups of **Max Muncy** and **Austin Riley**. While **Freeland** possesses the park-factor upside against Sugano, his assumed #9 spot in the lineup acts as a severe anchor on his efficiency score, making it difficult to justify a start over the high-leverage opportunities provided to **Riley** (71.42) against Taijuan Walker. We are closely monitoring the 31% rain probability in the Wacha and Pasquantino games; specifically, **Vinnie Pasquantino** (62.51) remains in the lineup for now, but owners should keep **Josh Naylor** (49.78) ready on the bench should the weather forecast deteriorate or the lineup remain unconfirmed as we approach first pitch.",
